This paper is about an online learning algorithm for ranking web pages based on the dependent click model (DCM). The DCM is a model commonly used in information retrieval (IR) and natural language processing (NLP) to describe user behavior when searching for information online. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories for this paper are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.IR (Information Retrieval), and cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the paper uses techniques from reinforcement learning (RL) and bandit algorithms, which are also relevant to the sub-categories cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
